{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0fb088c2-0b4f-4621-bd16-d6921e5fe41a","content":"Your project is set up correctly. The `IsValidEmail` method only checks for null/empty but doesn't check for `@`, so `Validate_MissingAtSign_ReturnsFalse` will fail.\n\nTo use hot reload for fast iteration, run:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts tests in **watch mode** — it runs your tests, then waits for file changes. When you save edits to `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (e.g., fixing `IsValidEmail` to check for `@`), it **hot-reloads** the changes and **re-runs tests automatically** without a full rebuild.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Run `dotnet test --hotreload` in a terminal\n2. See the failing test\n3. Fix the code (e.g., add `&& email.Contains('@')` to `IsValidEmail`)\n4. Save — tests re-run instantly\n5. Press `Ctrl+C` when done\n\nThis is much faster than running `dotnet test` repeatedly since it skips the full build/reload cycle.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7736a30f-7816-4438-bcf2-ed9d5d894286","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has the HotReload extension already in their project. They want to know how to use it to quickly iterate on fixes.\n\nLooking at the tests:\n1. `Validate_ValidEmail_ReturnsTrue` - passes (non-empty string with @)\n2. `Validate_MissingAtSign_ReturnsFalse` - FAILS because `IsValidEmail(\"userexample.com\")` returns `true` (it's not empty), but the test expects `false`\n3. `Validate_EmptyString_ReturnsFalse` - passes\n\nThe `IsValidEmail` method only checks for null/empty, not for the `@` sign.\n\n\nTo use the HotReload extension, I can run `dotnet test --hotreload` which will watch for file changes and automatically re-run the tests whenever I save changes, letting me quickly verify fixes without manual rebuilds.","outputTokens":606,"requestId":"341A:2D1D23:B71C8E:D6C3F9:69F404F8"},"id":"621f6f2f-522c-4bfa-bc35-5fb8f81ea1fe","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:42:29.801Z","parentId":"59ee81de-b8e4-46dc-80b0-4355ba35154e"}
